  "response_text": "# Daily Routine for a 70-Year-Old Kannadiga Gowda Man\n\n## Morning (6:00-8:30 AM)\n- **6:00 AM**: Wake up, drink warm water with lemon\n- **6:15 AM**: Light yoga or walk in fresh air (30 mins)\n- **6:45 AM**: Meditation or prayer (15 mins)\n- **7:00 AM**: Warm bath\n- **7:30 AM**: Breakfast\n\n## Breakfast (7:30 AM)\n**Traditional Gowda options:**\n- **Ragi mudde** (finger millet balls) with sambar or curry\n- **Jowar roti** with ghee and jaggery\n- **Akki roti** (rice flatbread) with vegetables\n- **Kanji** (fermented rice drink) for digestion\n- Warm milk with turmeric and honey\n\n## Mid-Morning (9:00-11:00 AM)\n- Light household activities\n- Social interaction/family time\n- Herbal tea (ginger, cumin, coriander)\n\n## Lunch (12:30-1:30 PM)\n**Main meal - Gowda style:**\n- **Rice or jowar** (staple)\n- **Dal curry** (moong, urad, or chana dal)\n- **Seasonal vegetable curry** (drumstick, pumpkin, beans)\n- **Pickle/achaar** (aids digestion)\n- **Buttermilk** or thin yogurt\n- Fresh fruit (seasonal)\n\n## Afternoon (2:00-4:00 PM)\n- Rest/light nap (30-45 mins)\n- Reading or hobby time\n- Gentle stretching\n\n## Evening (4:00-6:00 PM)\n- **4:00 PM**: Light snack\n  - Roasted groundnuts\n  - Homemade chikhalwali (puffed rice snack)\n  - Herbal tea (tulsi, ginger)\n- **5:00 PM**: Evening walk (20-30 mins)\n\n## Dinner (7:00-7:30 PM)\n**Light meal:**\n- **Ragi porridge** (finger millet) with jaggery\n- **Vegetable soup** with lentils\n- **Bajra roti** with mild curry\n- **Kanji** or buttermilk\n- Avoid heavy, spicy foods\n\n## Night (8:00-10:00 PM)\n- Light conversation/family time\n- Gentle digestion walk (10 mins)\n- Warm milk with cardamom and honey\n- Reading or prayer\n- **10:00 PM**: Sleep\n\n---\n\n## Nutritional Principles (Gowda Tradition)\n| Element | Benefits |\n|---------|----------|\n| **Millets** (ragi, jowar, bajra) | Fiber-rich, easier digestion |\n| **Ghee** | Warmth, joint health |\n| **Seasonal vegetables** | Natural immunity |\n| **Fermented foods** | Better digestion |\n| **Buttermilk** | Cooling, probiotic |\n| **Groundnuts** | Protein, healthy fats |\n\n## Weekly Additions\n- **Tuesday/Friday**: Include fish or chicken (if non-vegetarian)\n- **Sundays**: Traditional feast with extended family\n- **Seasonal**: Mango, sugarcane, fresh greens\n\n## Health Tips\n✓ Eat warm, freshly cooked food  \n✓ Avoid refrigerated/processed foods  \n✓ Drink adequate water (8-10 glasses)  \n✓ Include spices: turmeric, cumin, coriander  \n✓ Regular medical check-ups  \n✓ Maintain consistent meal times  \n\nThis routine honors Gowda agricultural traditions while supporting healthy aging.",
